This paper discusses the performance of various field-normalized bibliometric indicators, which are commonly used in computer science research. The paper specifically focuses on the biomedical area, which falls under the categories of digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), cybernetics (cs.CY), social and information networks (cs.SI), and cryptography and security (cs.CR). However, since the paper does not provide any specific focus on any of these sub-categories, it could potentially belong to any of them.
